quran[16]{c,v,t,f}:
36,55,"Indeed, the people of Paradise will be busy enjoying themselves: {1}",footnotes:1:To understand this one should remember that the righteous believers will not be withheld in the Plain of Resurrection
36,56,"they and their spouses shall be reclining on their couches in shady groves;"
36,57,"therein there will be all kinds of fruits to eat, and they shall have all that they desire."
36,58,"“Peace” shall be the word conveyed to them from their Merciful Lord."
36,59,"“Criminals, separate yourselves from others today! {1}",footnotes:1:This can have two meanings:
36,60,"Children of Adam, did I not command you not to serve Satan � he is to you an open enemy"
36,61,"and serve Me alone: this is the Straight Way? {1}",footnotes:1:Here again Allah has used ibadat (worship) in the sense of itaat (obedience). This subject has already been explained above in (Surah Al-Baqarah
36,62,"Still, he misguided a whole throng of you. Did you have no sense? {1}",footnotes:1:That is
36,63,"Now this is the Hell of which you were warned."
36,64,"Burn in it on account of your disbelieving."
36,65,"Today We shall put a seal on their mouths, and their hands will speak to Us and their feet shall bear witness to what they had been doing. {1}",footnotes:1:This command will be given in respect of the stubborn culprits
36,66,"If We so willed, We would have put out their eyes, then they would rush to see the Way, but how would they be able to see?"
36,67,"If We so willed, We would have transformed them where they were so that they would not go forward or backward. {1}",footnotes:1:After depicting the scene of Resurrection
36,68,"Whomsoever We grant a long life, We reverse him in his constitution. {1} Do they still not understand?",footnotes:1:“Reverse him in creation
36,69,"We did not teach him (to wit, the Messenger) poetry and it does not behove him. {1} This is none but an Admonition, and a Clear Book",footnotes:1:This is a rejoinder to the disbelievers
36,70,"that he may warn him who is alive {1} and establish an argument against those that deny the Truth.",footnotes:1:Every living person means: Every person who is capable of thinking and understanding
